#X text 17 21 [score2] has a 'tempo' syntax where 'tempo 60' sets the bpm to 60! You can also set a beat length with the 'beat' syntax as in 'beat 3/8' before the tempo message. The 'beat' and 'tempo' messages are output in the third 'data' outlet. You can also set 'tempo 90 3' as in this example and it will accelerate or deaccelerate \, going from whatever bpm setting you have to '90' in three beats. When changing the tempo speed \, tempo values for each beat are also output., f 42;
#X text 17 404 A bang is sent at the rightmost outlet when the sequence is over. An 'end' message is also output in the data outlet if you're not looping. See about looping in the next example though., f 41;
